list.item:
•Testosterone Gel, 1.62% is contraindicated in women who are pregnant. Testosterone Gel, 1.62% can cause virilization of the female fetus when administered to a pregnant woman. Pregnant women need to be aware of the potential for transfer of testosterone from men treated with Testosterone Gel, 1.62%. If a pregnant woman is exposed to Testosterone Gel, 1.62%, she should be apprised of the potential hazard to the fetus [see Warnings and Precautions (5.2) and 

   Use in Specific Populations (8.1)

].

text.paragraph:
Due to the lack of controlled evaluations in women and potential virilizing effects, Testosterone Gel, 1.62% is not indicated for use in women [see Contraindications (4) and Use in Specific Populations (8.1, 

                              8.2

                           )].
